President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of Washington due to a severe storm, straight-line winds, and flooding that occurred on July 20, 2012. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected area. Federal funding is available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Kenneth K. Suiso has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments.